<sec id="sec1-1755738013488269"><title>Best of five question</title>
<p>A 30-year-old man attends after noticing a neck lump for the past 6 weeks. He complains of fatigue and night-sweats.</p>
<p>On examination there is a firm swelling in the left posterior triangle. It is deep to the skin with no erythema or punctum.</p>
<p><bold>What is the SINGLE MOST likely diagnosis in this patient? Select ONE option only.</bold>
<list id="list1-1755738013480022" list-type="alpha-upper">
<list-item><p>Abscess</p></list-item>
<list-item><p>Infected sebaceous cyst</p></list-item>
<list-item><p>Lymphoma</p></list-item>
<list-item><p>Thyroglossal cyst</p></list-item>
<list-item><p>Toxic thyroid nodule</p></list-item>
</list></p>
